## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="e26c6-102">Esta extensión solo aparece en los servicios alojados en IIS o WAS.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e26c6-102">This extension is present only for services hosted in IIS or WAS.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e26c6-103">Los servicios pueden determinar si se hospedan en IIS o WAS recuperando esta extensión de su <xref:System.ServiceModel.ServiceHostBase>, como se muestra en el ejemplo siguiente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e26c6-103">Services can determine whether they are hosted in IIS or WAS by retrieving this extension from their <xref:System.ServiceModel.ServiceHostBase>, as shown in the following example.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="e26c6-104">El ejemplo siguiente muestra cómo recuperar el <xref:System.ServiceModel.Activation.VirtualPathExtension> del host de servicio y devolver un valor que se hospede en IIS o WAS.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e26c6-104">The following example shows how to recover the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Activation.VirtualPathExtension> from the service host and return a value that it is hosted in IIS or WAS.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
bool isHosted = false;  
ServiceHostBase host = OperationContext.Current.Host;  
VirtualPathExtension vpe = host.Extentions.Find<VirtualPathExtension>();  
  
if( vpe != null )  
Console.WriteLine("The virtualPath of the hosted Service is  {0}", vpe.VirtualPath);  
```
